<span id="freeTextContainer7914861916072488476">Historically it&apos;s a mess. There is virtually no character development. The writing style is pretty pulpy with non-stop action and it&apos;s an easy escapist read. There are other Roman series out there far superior. Iggulden may improve as he writes more books, but he&apos;s not my &apos;cup of tea&apos; from this one and I have no desire to read any more of his novels.</span>
  <span id="freeText7914861916072488476" style="display:none">Historically it's a mess. There is virtually no character development. The writing style is pretty pulpy with non-stop action and it's an easy escapist read. There are other Roman series out there far superior. Iggulden may improve as he writes more books, but he's not my 'cup of tea' from this one and I have no desire to read any more of his novels.</span>
